<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Gardeltron</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Oracle<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Nov 2000<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>This post is a very important illustration of the effects of repeated lackluster expansions on the power of a shaman.  If we had kept pace with other classes, it would not be an issue.  Yes, shaman buffs can help other classes, but in the case of these trials, shamans do not bring enough DPS to the group to be desireable.<br />
<br />
This is as true of the most uber shamans as it is of the rest of us.  When I was getting flagged, Chukzombi's magister group was ahead of us.  It had two shamans in it (pretty sure Mukas was one, can't remember if the other was Chuk or Warren).  Both shamans were decked out with the latest VT gear, both had ancient scourge, etc.  Their group failed at least twice while I was there, maybe even more.<br />
<br />
When I got flagged, the only thing I did was heal and sick my dog on mobs (didn't have the 61 pet then).   My nukes were a waste, slow was barely effective.  We had a wizard and druid nuking, an SK tank, a rogue, and an enchanter for mezzing.  As it was, I was barely able to keep the tank alive with Kragg (didn't have Tnarg), and was unable to save the enchanter.<br />
<br />
I've done a few trials since then to try and help others get through, but found that the best thing I could do to help was buff then get the heck out of the way.  It is gratifying to see a group that almost wins without your buffs be able to win with them, but disturbing that you can't do any more than that to help.<br />
<br />
The fact that the only thing people want from shamans in the PoJ trials is buffs is symptomatic the loss in relative power in the class.  I seriously doubt that LoY will rectify this.  Perhaps the promise of additional priest class balancing by SOE will help out here.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91769" target="_blank">Heyokah Gardeltron Thundercrag</a><br />
Prodigal Soothsayer of <a href="http://www.afflictionguild.com" target="_blank">Affliction</a><br />
Erollisi Marr</div>
	
