	<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		
		<td class="smallfont"><b>Shammies not useless...</b></td>
		<td class="smallfont" align="right" wrap="nowrap">Post #<b><a href="showpost.php?s=dcc0c6dbab3f3cd4941f8f081eb6adb8&amp;postid=122613&postcount=19" target="new">19</a></b></td>
	</tr>
	</table>
	<!-- /2 -->
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Xev_Grammar</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jul 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Shammies aren't useless in a specific type of trial group at least.  I was in a group with two magicians, an enchanter, a warrior, a cleric, and myself.  Since there was only one tank I could use torpor to maximum advantage, healing everyone except the tank efficiently with torpor.<br />
<br />
I kept my mana up easily with canni and modrods, and I was able to contribute effectively with spear of torment and my dogdog who was armed with weapons.  It was definitely poor dps compared to the magician damage.  But I also kept the cleric and the casters alive.  I never had to cure slow in my successful trial but that would've been key as well.  I used my DDs when I was full mana, or when the tank called to nuke hard (in case the prisoner was close to dying)-- there was once or twice when it was close and my quick nuke was important in keeping the trial going.<br />
<br />
I slowed the executioner.  That was important in itself.  I don't remember but I might've crippled him too.  I broke out the Spirit Call brigade.  I assisted the cleric with heals, and he went oom, and I continued to heal the tank so that he could last a lot longer.<br />
<br />
Eventually the executioner enraged and I let the tank die just because I ran out of mana and couldn't keep up.<br />
<br />
But the chanter got off the killing nuke and the tank was rezd at the end. hehe.<br />
<br />
This was done at level 61 with kragg's mending and torpor.  I'd imagine it would be even easier with tnarg's at 62.<br />
<br />
Add to that our useful buffage, I would hardly say a shammy was useless.<br />
<br />
I was lucky I guess, it was only my second real attempt (four attempts altogether, two I really tried).<br />
<br />
I would kick a guildy's ass if he did that to me (unless he was apologetic about it-- then I'd just be pissed but I wouldn't kick his ass).</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />---<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=576270" target="_blank">Grammar</a>, Ogre Shaman (Xev Server)</div>
	
	
